Result:

Achievements & Behaviors
1. Acting Responsibly to Inspire Trust

Delivered multiple business-critical fixes and enhancements in RCADE, GDP, and RPDIL, including regulatory fixes (e.g., dispersion chart issue, scheduled publication fixes, PDF page count logic). These were implemented well before timelines, demonstrating accountability and reliability.

Took ownership of production support and compliance-driven tasks, including Admin UI auditing for RCADE, certificate onboarding in Certhub, and EXACC migration for RPDIL. These contributions ensured audit readiness, operational continuity, and risk mitigation.

Actively participated in eBCM activities, supporting the primary coordinator to meet deadlines and compliance requirements without any overdue actions.

Earned trust from stakeholders by proactively engaging with Business, Control Room, and Analyst Hub to resolve critical issues and clarify requirements.

2. Thinking Commercially for Sustainable Outcomes

Designed and implemented the Synopsis functionality in GDP, moving away from manual SQL updates to an automated UI-based approach, which improved efficiency and reduced operational risk.

Contributed to GDP enhancements such as multithreaded blocking queue processing to improve system stability, and onboarding of new TPA clients (e.g., AIERA), which expanded the client distribution reach.

Supported OCP4 upstream migration for RCADE and RPDIL by delivering critical configuration changes, ensuring smooth rollout and long-term system sustainability.

Partnered with management and business users to design the Email Distribution Service using Adobe Experience Platform, aligning technical implementation with long-term strategic goals for client communication.

3. Taking Initiative to Create Solutions

Took the lead in Adobe Integration POC, exploring Adobe Experience Platform (AEP), gathering requirements, creating demo use cases, and presenting findings to leadership. This proactive effort gave management confidence in the new email distribution approach and earned Rajesh the India Individual Excellence Award (IB AFCC).

Implemented innovative fixes in RCADE, such as new logic for page count validation, enhanced snapshot distribution logic, and historical chart RCA. These solutions simplified processes and improved reliability.

Proposed and implemented Excel attachment support for Internal Reware channel and contributed to client channel update requests in DBExchange, creating new opportunities to serve clients effectively.

Participated in Global Hackathon, showcasing innovation mindset and willingness to challenge the status quo.

4. Working Collectively for the Greatest Impact

Collaborated with upstream teams on F4 remediation and reconciliation processes, ensuring smooth cross-team delivery.

Worked closely with Business and Analyst Hub teams on features such as CML scan changes and regulatory fixes, combining technical expertise with open dialogue to deliver timely outcomes.

Partnered with Adobe SMEs to deepen understanding of AEP fundamentals and helped other IB teams explore use cases, acting as a trusted SME.

Actively participated in CSR activity (Power of One), contributing to social initiatives like making paper bags for NGOs, reflecting fairness, inclusivity, and collective responsibility.

Owned and executed Disaster Recovery (DR) activities for RCADE and GDP seamlessly, working with stakeholders to ensure smooth execution without any disruption.

